Task 4: Predicting Insurance Claim Amounts (Regression)
Objective: Estimate medical insurance costs based on personal and demographic data.

Key Skills: Linear Regression, Multi-variable Correlation, Error Evaluation (MAE/RMSE).


Technical Challenges Overcome: Resolved a FileNotFoundError by implementing proper relative path resolution for the insurance.csv dataset.

Outcome: A regression model capable of estimating claims with measured error margins, highlighting the heavy impact of smoking on insurance premiums.
